sentences: Renée Morisset,  (June 13, 1928 – May 3, 2009) was a Canadian pianist.
In 1964, she and her husband were awarded the Prix Calixa-Lavallée.

In 1981, she and her husband were made Members of the Order of Canada in recognition of having "contributed to" Canada's "musical life by attracting attention to the works of Canadian composers-works that were composed especially for them-and through their participation in various cultural organizations".
In 1985, they were promoted to Officer.
In 1994, they were made Knights of the National Order of Quebec.
